	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64641292"><p><div class="quote"><p>That said, it's good to know that at least a few companies do get off the update treadmill.</p></div><p>Yes if you run a system with the network capabilities of carrier pigeon you can get off the update treadmill. On the flip side if you run a system that is actually capable of connecting to a network then the "update treadmill" is part of security.</p><p>We live in a world of zero day attacks. If you're afraid of a Crowdstrike (because it happened once) and therefore decide not to update your systems (bad actor attacks happen daily) then you have a serious risk management problem.</p></div>
	</div>

