	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64641014"><p>What we have here is a known problem, called the <a href="https://press.princeton.edu/books/paperback/9780691004129/normal-accidents" title="princeton.edu">"Normal Accident Theory."</a> [princeton.edu] As systems get more and more complex, eventually, something is going to come into conflict at some point.

</p><p>It's also "big news" because people are mad about the airline delays. But let's be honest, CrowdStrike's competitors can be far worse. McAfee causes wide-ranging Windows BSOD issues at least yearly, they just had one outbreak in January.</p></div>
	</div>

