	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64640914">Isn't MS-Windows 3.1 also in use in most ATM's?  It's far less feature-rich than its higher version number relatives, but the simplicity allows the existing security issues to be identified and addressed.  3.1 didn't have its own network stack, I remember running the Trumpet network connector to implement TCP/IP networking under Windows 3.1 (i.e., the networking component isn't Microsoft technology, technically speaking).  Also, ATM's don't need 95% of what Windows 3.1 even offered, it's being used in a hig</div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64640914">

